The paper deals with the problem of generalizing data in a way that preserves privacy, which is a common concern in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The specific types of data being generalized are geographic and geometric, which suggests categories such as computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
